Only feature releases go to all the lists.
Bug fix releases only go to the CGAL announce
and discuss lists.


Mailing lists:

  *********************************************************************
  ** Note: add a Reply-To: cgal-discuss@inria.fr, to avoid           **
  ** cross-post replies.                                             **
  *********************************************************************

  cgal-develop@inria.fr (best sent as blind carbon copy)
  cgal-discuss@inria.fr
  cgal-announce@inria.fr

And only for feature releases (not bug-fixes):

  compgeom-announce@inria.fr
  mesh@sandia.gov
  communaute@medicis.polytechnique.fr




Newsgroups:

  sci.image.processing,
  comp.graphics.algorithms,
  comp.robotics.misc,
  comp.infosystems.gis


Moderated newsgroups:

  comp.simulation,
  comp.robotics.research

Note that comp.simulation disallow cross-posting to more than three
groups. And there must be a followup-to. And one cannot cross-post between
moderated groups.

The best may be:
  1/ cross-post to
        sci.image.processing,comp.graphics.algorithms,comp.infosystems.gis 
  2/ cross-post to 
        comp.robotics.misc,comp.robotics.research
     with fu2 comp.robotics.misc
  3/ single-post to
         comp.simulation
